The Munich FIDE Women's Grand Prix is a 12-player round-robin taking place in Munich, Germany on February 2-13, 2023. It forms the second of four stages of the 2022-23 FIDE Women's Grand Prix, which will determine two places in the 2023 Candidates Tournament. 16 players compete in the series, each playing in three of the four events.

Players receive 90 minutes for 40 moves, followed by 30 minutes to the end of the game, plus a 30-second increment starting from move one. The prize fund is 80,000 euros, with 15,000 euros and 160 Grand Prix points for the winner. No draw offers are allowed before move 30. Official website: womengrandprix.fide.com
